property wln.btenabled
'<b>R/O PROPERTY (ENUM, BYTE), DEFAULT VALUE= 0- NO.</b>
'<br><br>
'Powers on/off the bluetooth interface. 
'<br><br>
'The bluetooth hardware becomes operational after the user calls wln.boot, sets wln.btenabled and the power on event occurs. wln.boot must be called before enabling bluetooth. 
'<br><br>
'The bluetooth interface is disabled and the wln.btenabled is reset to 0- NO if the Wi-Fi/Bluetooth hardware is disconnected, powered down, malfunctioned,
'or was intentionally reset. When this happens, the on_wln_bt_event event is generated, too.
    get = syscall(752) as no_yes
    set = syscall(753) (value as no_yes)
end property


